comment8_en = "The Boyu Tokaido was designed just to connect Tokyo and Kyoto, but the government had to do quite a bit to assuage fears and concerns of tunneling under Mt. Fuji."
comment8_jp = "とにかく東京と京都を結ぶ事だけを考えて設計した卯酉東海道だったが、政府は霊峰富士の真下に穴を開けるという、畏れ多き事態だけは避けた。"
comment7_en = "      \"Stop worrying so much. Just have a drink and stop being so pessimistic.\n      When Mt. Fuji was recognized as a World Heritage Site, they designated it as an extinct volcano, so it's no longer merely dormant. Remember?\""
comment7_jp = "      「心配性ね。そういう時はお酒でも飲んで考えるのをやめましょう？\n      富士が世界遺産に認定された時に、休火山から死火山になったと断定されたでしょう？」"
comment6_en = "   \"Oh, I see, so we're under Mt. Fuji.\n   But I do know about Mt. Fuji. It's been said there's an entrance to the Netherworld underneath it since ancient times.\n   But it's a volcano, isn't it? I wonder if it was safe to build a tunnel here.\""
comment6_jp = "   「なるほど、富士山の地下ね。\n   なら判らないでもないわ。昔から富士の地下には冥界の入り口があるって言うもんね。\n   でも、富士山って火山でしょう？　そんな地下にトンネルなんて掘って大丈夫なのかなぁ」"
comment5_en = "      \"Ah, perhaps we're under the sacred mountain.\n      The atmosphere is a little different... No, wait, it might even be the dimension that's different.\n      You're such a worry-wart that it's making you overly nervous.\""
comment5_jp = "      「ああ、それはきっとここが霊峰の下だからよ。\n      少しは空気も違う、いや時空すらも異なるかも知れないわね。\n      過敏なメリーにはちょっと緊張が走るかも知れないわ」"
comment4_en = "   \"I suddenly felt kinda sick.\n   Don't you feel it, Renko? The space we're now is a bit different from normal.\n   Also, I can see a gap in the border... Maybe it's a bug in the screen-controlling program?\""
comment4_jp = "   「急に頭が重くなった気がしたの。\n   蓮子は感じない？　ここら辺の空間は少し他と感じが違うわよ。\n   それに結界の裂け目も見える……スクリーン制御プログラムのバグかしら」"
comment3_en = "      \"What's the matter, Merry? You look scary all of a sudden.\""
comment3_jp = "      「どうしたの？　メリー、急に怖い顔をして……」"
comment2_en = "   \"Ah, I...\""
comment2_jp = "   「あ、今……」"

[06]
name_jp = "お宇佐さまの素い幡"
name_en = "White Flag of Lord Usa"
comment11_en = "However, Hiroshige was also rather fascinated with it."
comment11_jp = "しかし、広重もまた、富士に魅入られた者だった。"
comment10_en = "After that, a young Utagawa Hiroshige, who was only half his age, published The Fifty-three Stations of the Tokaido which became more popular. Undaunted, Hokusai also published his Hundred Views of Mount Fuji despite the thirty-six edition he released earlier.\nThat is how obsessed he was with Mt. Fuji."
comment10_jp = "自分の半分くらいの年齢しか無い、若い広重が『東海道五十三次』を出版し、それが人気を博すと、過去に三十六景を出したというのに、負けじと北斎は『富嶽百景』を出版した。\nその位、富士に魅入られていたのだ。"
comment9_en = "Speaking of Fuji, the Thirty-six Views of Mount Fuji Katsushika Hokusai created is well-known, yet he was not satisfied with any of the pictures of Mt. Fuji he drew. You can tell this because he actually drew forty-six pictures."
comment9_jp = "富士と言えば北斎の『富嶽三十六景』が有名であるが、北斎は富士を幾ら描こうとも満足することはなかった。富嶽三十六景は実際には四十六枚ある事からも判る。"
comment8_en = "      \"By the way, do you know what kind of okura they mean in the phrase okura-iri?\""
comment8_jp = "      「そういえば、『お蔵入り』の蔵って、何の蔵なのか知ってる？」"
comment7_en = "   \"Shouldn't they have realized it from the beginning?\n   Have you been fooled by some Hachiman-sama lover ?\""
comment7_jp = "   「そんなこと、最初から判りそうなものなのに……。\n   蓮子は誰かに嘘情報吹き込まれたんじゃないの？　八幡様が好きな誰かに」"
comment6_en = "      \"That's why it was okura-iri (suspended).\""
comment6_jp = "      「ま、そういう理由でお蔵入りになったらしいんだけどね」"
comment5_en = "   \"That seems like it would have been warm. Wait, Kamakura isn't a capital, is it?\n   And Kamakura is too close to Tokyo to be a stop between Kyoto and Tokyo.\""
comment5_jp = "   「暖かそうな新幹線ね。って、鎌倉は都じゃないでしょ？\n   それに鎌倉って、京都と東京の間にしては東京寄り過ぎじゃないの」"
comment4_en = "      \"Because I do, you know.\n      I heard they wanted to connect the three capitals and name it the Keito Shinkansen.\""
comment4_jp = "      「そりゃ、物知りだもの。\n      なんでも、三つの都を繋いで名前も繋都（けいと）新幹線にしたかったんだって」"
comment3_en = "   \"You seem to know everything, Renko.\""
comment3_jp = "   「蓮子は物知りねぇ」"
comment2_en = "      \"Ha ha, sake tastes pretty good in the morning.\n      Now that I think about it, this Shinkansen was originally designed to stop at Kamakura, too.\""
comment2_jp = "      「あはは。朝からお酒が美味しいわね。\n      そういえばこの新幹線、最初は京都と東京だけじゃなくて、鎌倉にも駅を作る予定だったらしいよ？」"

[07]
name_jp = "月まで届け、不死の煙"
name_en = "Reach for the Moon, Immortal Smoke"
comment14_en = "The Shinkansen would definitely provide an insane illusion for 36 minutes that would take you to your destination faster than the current one."
comment14_jp = "きっと、今よりも目的地に早く着く、36分間の狂気の幻想を愉しめたに違いない。"
comment13_en = "But, if this Shinkansen weren't Hiroshige but Hokusai, what kind of pictures would the kaleido-screen show?"
comment13_jp = "だがしかし、もしこの新幹線がヒロシゲではなく、ホクサイだったとしたら、カレイドスクリーンにはどういう情景が映し出されていただろうか。"
comment12_en = "The reason the Japanese have chosen Hiroshige is because they couldn't understand the talent of Hokusai. They hated his insanity with a passion."
comment12_jp = "日本が広重を選択したのは北斎の奇才を認める事が出来なかったからである。日本は狂気を徹底的に嫌ったのだ。"
comment11_en = "The genuine Mt. Fuji became more beautiful through the efforts of the Mount Fuji Revival Association. However, due to the strict guidelines they put in place, that turned off a lot of people from climbing it, so the tourist association took a big hit. How ironic."
comment11_jp = "本物の富士山も、富士山復興会の努力により今は綺麗である。本来の富士の姿の余りの迫力に圧倒されたか、復興会の厳しい掟に嫌気がさしたか、山を登る人の姿も少なくなり、観光協会が大打撃を受けたというのは皮肉だが。"
comment10_en = "The scenery with few buildings through the Kaleido-screen showed the sacred and dynamic Mt.Fuji."
comment10_jp = "建物の少ないカレイドスクリーンの景色では、富士山は霊験あらたかで、迫力のある姿を見せていた。"
comment9_en = "   \"Oh, dear.\""
comment9_jp = "   「あらあら」"
comment8_en = "      \"Even the name was almost the same, only differing in the kanji, Thirty-six Views of Mt. Fuji. It was published after Hokusai died.\""
comment8_jp = "      「その名も、『富士（不二）三十六景』というの。しかも北斎の没後に出版したのよ」"
comment7_en = "   \"Oh, was it an imitation or an inspiration?\""
comment7_jp = "   「あら、パクリ？　インスパイア？」"
comment6_en = "      \"Merry, do you know that Hiroshige also antagonized Hokusai by creating his own thirty-six views of Mt. Fuji?\""
comment6_jp = "      「メリー、広重も北斎に対抗して、富士の三十六景を描いていたってのは知っている？」"
comment5_en = "   \"To me, this Fuji looks more like the one Hokusai drew than that of Hiroshige.\n   Its scale is also a process of automatic video re-targeting.\n   It makes much of an impact than the real one.\""
comment5_jp = "   「この富士は、広重と言うよりは北斎かなぁ。\n   スケールだって、オートマチックビデオリターゲッティングの処理された様な感じがするわ。\n   リアリティよりインパクトを重視した様な気がする」"
comment4_en = "      \"Hmmm... I can't say for sure since I've never really had a close look at the real one, but I think they're about the same.\n      If the real one didn't have any man-made objects around it, I believe it would look something like this.\""
comment4_jp = "      「うーん。余りまじまじと実物を見た事がないから何とも言えないけど、こんな感じだと思うわよ？\n      きっと、周りに人工物が殆ど映っていないと、こんな感じに見えるんじゃないかな」"
comment3_en = "   \"Renko, the Mt. Fuji displayed in the walls of the tunnel is a bit too dynamic, isn't it?\""
comment3_jp = "   「ねぇ蓮子。トンネルスクリーンに映ってる富士山って、ちょっとダイナミック過ぎないかしら？」"
comment2_en = "In the end, the Japanese now have chosen Utagawa Hiroshige.\nThe Boyu Shinkansen Hiroshige continues to run for eastward. It is likely around Kamakura by now."
comment2_jp = "何にしても現代の日本は広重を選んだのだ。\n卯酉新幹線ヒロシゲは、地下を東に走り続ける。今はちょうど鎌倉辺りだろうか。"

[08]
name_jp = "レトロスペクティブ京都"
name_en = "Retrospective Kyoto"
comment11_en = "Tokyo is about to return to its roots."
comment11_jp = "東京は昔の姿を取り戻しつつある。"
comment10_en = "Tokyo is an unique city where flashy young people make their own rules.\nLike the town where Machi-yakko, Hatamoto-yakko and Hiseshi run wild..."
comment10_jp = "派手な格好の若者達が、独自のルールを形成している事が特徴的な東京。\n町奴や旗本奴、火消しが暴れる町の様に……。"
comment9_en = "Even inside the perimeter of the Yamanote Line, a strange field is starting to form. Not leafy plants, but curious flowers made of nothing but stalk and petals are covering the roads. The number of the old-fashioned vehicle called the car has decreased along with the decrease in population. Even if anything major happened to the roads, it would not be an inconvenience."
comment9_jp = "環状線も一部が草原と化し、葉っぱもなく、茎と赤い花弁だけの奇妙な花が道を覆いつつある。人口の減少と共に、自動車という前時代的な乗り物も減っていた。道がどうなろうと不便な事は無かったのだ。"
comment8_en = "As the sins of the spirits trapped in the earth by asphalt are fading away, there are a lot of cracks in the roads of Tokyo."
comment8_jp = "アスファルトで固められた地霊の罪も時効を迎え、東京の道のそこら中にひびが入っていた。"
comment7_en = "      \"Tokyo is a spiritual city just like Kyoto, so we'll be able to have a great time.\n      Because I'm with you, Merry.\""
comment7_jp = "      「東京は、京都に負けず劣らずの霊都だから、きっと楽しいわ。\n      メリーと一緒なら」"
comment6_en = "   \"Wait. Weren't we going to visit the Netherworld?\""
comment6_jp = "   「あれ？　冥界参りに行くんだっけ？」"
comment5_en = "      \"Don't be in such a hurry.\n      First, I need to go home, finish the visit of my family's grave for Higan, then once we find a place for our luggage, we'll go sightseeing, OK?\""
comment5_jp = "      「そう焦らないの。\n      まずは実家に着いてから彼岸の墓参りを済ませて、荷物を置いてから見学に行きましょう？」"
comment4_en = "   \"Well, as long as we'll have more time for sightseeing of Tokyo, it's OK.\n   Where were you going to show me around?\""
comment4_jp = "   「ま、東京見物出来る時間が増えたから良いか。\n   今日はどんなところを案内してくれるの？」"
comment3_en = "      \"You're right, still it's better not to be tired before the arrival.\""
comment3_jp = "      「確かにね。でも着く前に疲れなくて良いじゃない」"
comment2_en = "   \"I hope we'll arrive in Tokyo soon.\n   What a dull journey...\""
comment2_jp = "   「もうすぐ東京かしら。\n   やっぱり物足りないわね」"

[09]
name_jp = "ラクトガール　～ 少女密室"
name_en = "Locked Girl ~ Girl's Secret Room"
comment11_en = "As Merry had only seen it in books, the closer she came to Tokyo, the town exceeding time, the more excited she got."
comment11_jp = "本でしか見た事の無い、時代を超えた街、東京に近づくにつれて、メリーの気持ちがますます高揚した。"
comment10_en = "The city Tokyo is the genuine successor of Edo."
comment10_jp = "江戸の血を確実に引く東京の街。"
comment9_en = "Ever since the Edo era, Tokyo has had eating competitions, where gluttons would eat as if they were unafraid of death by overeating. With that in mind, it seems obvious how present Tokyo could turn out these food theme parks."
comment9_jp = "東京には、江戸時代の頃から、闘食会と呼ばれた死をも恐れない食の大会があった。それを考えると、現代の東京で食のテーマパークが流行るのも当然の事である。"
comment8_en = "The food theme parks in Tokyo used to be found all over Japan.\nWith each store selling delicious flavors from all over the country all in one place, they seemed to be rather undignified theme parks. Even so, they are still very popular in Tokyo."
comment8_jp = "東京にはその昔、食のテーマパークが流行った時代があった。\n全国各地から美味しいと評判の店を持ってきて、一箇所に集めただけという何とも風情の無いテーマパークだったが、それでも東京の人間には大好評だった。"
comment7_en = "   \"But I like green tea.\n   Especially when the tearooms are secretive.\""
comment7_jp = "   「あら、お茶は好きよ？\n   あの茶室の密室さ加減が」"
comment6_en = "      \"That's because Kyoto is too uptight.\n      Their idea of entertainment are things like modern tea ceremonies.\""
comment6_jp = "      「その辺、京都は厳しいからねぇ。\n      娯楽と言えば新茶道とかしかないし」"
comment5_en = "   \"Those sound nice. Such unrefined entertainment still exists here.\""
comment5_jp = "   「良いわねぇ。その洗練されていない庶民的な娯楽がまだ残っているのね」"
comment4_en = "      \"Amusement parks in tall buildings that have a feeling of confinement and massive shopping malls.\""
comment4_jp = "      「閉塞感ある狭くて高いビルの中で遊ぶテーマパークとか、超大型ショッピングモールとか」"
comment3_en = "   \"For example?\""
comment3_jp = "   「例えば？」"
comment2_en = "      \"Unlike Kyoto, Tokyo is rural so there are many nostalgic things.\""
comment2_jp = "      「京都と違って東京は田舎だから、懐かしい物が沢山あるのよ」"

[10]
name_jp = "千年幻想郷　～ History of the Moon"
name_en = "Gensokyo Millennium ~ History of the Moon"
comment11_en = "The world returned to darkness when the final sentence \"Designed by Utagawa Hiroshige\" appeared in the middle of the screen."
comment11_jp = "風景の真ん中に「Designed by Utagawa Hiroshige」と言う文章が浮かんだのを最後に、世界は闇に閉ざされた。"
comment10_en = "Even so, human beings insist that scenery is theirs. Along the scenery that all the passengers likely believed to have been actual footage, the developers' name of the three-dimensional picture continued to appear and vanish."
comment10_jp = "それでも、人間は自分の物だと主張する。乗客は皆、本物の景色ではないかと思って見ていた立体的な風景に、映像の制作者の名前が浮かんでは消え、消えては浮かんでいる。"
comment9_en = "By nature, scenery doesn't belong to anybody. In addition, the imagery is based on the Tokaido that Hiroshige probably saw."
comment9_jp = "本来、景色には誰の著作物である、という考え方は無い。さらに言うと、この映像は広重が見たであろう東海道を基にしているのだ。"
comment8_en = "Words were displayed on the scenery through of windows.\nIt meant the end of the 53-minute film."
comment8_jp = "窓の外の景色に文字が浮かび上がっている。\n53分のカレイドスクリーンの映像が、終わりを迎えようとしていた。"
comment7_en = "   \"Oh, it's the credits.\n   They even try to claim credit for the scenery displayed here.\""
comment7_jp = "   「あ、スタッフロールよ。\n   こんな風景まで作者の権利を主張しようとするのねぇ」"
comment6_en = "      \"They've ignored the gaps in their boundary.\n      The study of spirits has been carried out for over one thousand years in Kyoto.\""
comment6_jp = "      「結界の切れ目もほったらかしだしね。\n      千年以上も霊的研究を続けてきた京都とは大違いだから」"
comment5_en = "   \"Isn't it fine to act silly once in a while?\""
comment5_jp = "   「たまには馬鹿になるのも良いじゃない」"
comment4_en = "      \"Of course, 'cause it's me.\n      Still, I can't deny Tokyo is mentally immature to Kyoto.\""
comment4_jp = "      「そりゃ私の話だもの。\n      でもね、京都に比べるとやっぱり、精神的に未熟な都市って感じは否めないわ」"
comment3_en = "   \"After listening to you talk about it, I'm so excited to see it, Renko.\""
comment3_jp = "   「蓮子の話を聞いていたら、なんだか楽しみになってきたわ。東京が」"
comment2_en = "      \"Mt. Fuji is getting smaller. That means we're near Tokyo.\""
comment2_jp = "      「富士が小さくなっていくわ。もう東京は目の前ね」"

[11]
name_jp = "最も澄みわたる空と海"
name_en = "The Purest Sky and Sea"
comment6_en = "They came above ground and left Bo-Tokyo Station, continuing their non-altruistic 53-minute conversation."
comment6_jp = "53分間の他愛の無い会話の続きを地上でする為に、二人は東京駅を後にした。"
comment5_en = "   Though my body has vanished with flowers,\n   My spirit flies with its fragrance."
comment5_jp = "   身は華と与に落ちぬれども\n   心は香と将に飛ぶ"
comment4_en = "Needless to say, virtuality is the essence of human."
comment4_jp = "言うまでもなく、ヴァーチャルが人間の本質なのだ。"
comment3_en = "Nowadays, nobody would believe something as old-fashioned as that.\nVirtual sensations stimulates people more than real ones.\nJust as they cannot distinguish between dreams and reality, and humans from butterflies.\nIt's common sense in these days that these two elements can never be separated."
comment3_jp = "という前時代的な認識を持つ人間は、もはや居ないだろう。\nヴァーチャルの感覚は、リアルより人間の感覚を刺激する。\n夢と現は区別出来ない様に、人間と胡蝶は区別出来ない様に、\nヴァーチャルとリアルは決して区別出来ない、と言うのが今の常識である。"
comment2_en = "Even the highest dynamic range images,\nand the most Japanesque scenery,\nare not better than the true color of the sky."
comment2_jp = "ハイダイナミックレンジの映像も、\n極めて日本的な情景も、\n本物の空の色には敵わない。"